The moment I heard about this book on @the.sap podcast, I knew I needed this in my life. 

I'm paid to be a perfectionist, and while there is nothing wrong with having this mentality, there is a time and a place. It's the reason why people bring opportunities and projects to you, because they know that whatever you produce will be excellent! But it can also be a debilitating mindset, if you let the fear of your perceived failure keep you from taking risks or trying new things.

Highly suggest for all of my organizer AND artist friends out there. And it's a workbook, so get that journal open and pen poised!

node.text:
Want a quick and delicious guacamole recipe? This is one of my personal favorites that I made it with the homies @CAConover and @KrollTheWarriorKing on #ForkKnifeLive ? 
.
*Ingredients*
.
- Avocados: 4 (quartered, seeds and skin removed)
- Garlic: 1 tsp (minced)
- Lemon: 1 (juiced)
- Lime: 2 (juiced)
- Salt: 2 tblsp (plus more to taste)
- Roma tomatoes: 1pc (diced small)
- Red Onion: 1/4pc (diced small)
- Cilantro: 1/2 cup (chopped with stems)
- Jalapeño: 1/4 (chopped small with seeds)
- Corn: 1/2 ear, off the cob (kernels only)
.
*Directions*
.
- In a large mixing bowl, combine the avocados, garlic, lemon, lime and 1 tablespoon of salt. Mash until no more large chunks of avocado are left
- Add rest of ingredients and mix well
